      • write

        public void write(int offsetInBytes,
                  byte[] data)
           throws STException
        This function writes some bytes into the NDEF file. It can be used when the caller wants to handle the file selection himself. PREREQUISITE: The caller is responsible for selecting the NDEF file before calling this function.
        Parameters:
        offsetInBytes - Offset in Bytes from the beginning of the file.
        data - Data to write
        Throws:
        STException
